{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17491034","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17491034"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T05:29:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T05:29:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"810"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"810","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/810"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.19,0.49,0.23,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"810"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55611"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"810","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/810"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"810"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41151"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"461"},{"type":"tags","id":"1139"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"2545"},{"type":"tags","id":"2589"},{"type":"tags","id":"3455"},{"type":"tags","id":"6275"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"9644"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"684"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13976"},{"type":"contributions","id":"16044"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37998"},{"type":"contributions","id":"47863"},{"type":"contributions","id":"48148"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55611","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/55611"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 68-year-old man is brought into the Emergency Department after a fall. He has been feeling increasingly tired recently and then tripped over the carpet. He looks pale and the only abnormal physical finding is a Virchow\u0027s node. His haemoglobin is 63g/L with an iron deficiency picture. A CT scan is performed (Images 1, 2, 3).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Carcinoma of the lung","Carcinoma of the oesophagus","Carcinoma of the stomach","Hepatocellular carcinoma","Carcinoma of the pancreas"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAn enlarged and painless supraclavicular lymph node (Virchow) can be a worrying sign, particularly in an older patient. This finding is often the first sign of metastatic spread from an intra-abdominal or intra-thoracic neoplasm. In this case, the underlying disease appears to be a carcinoma of the oesophagus. The CT scan shows a \u003Cstrong\u003Ebulky tumour in the mid-oesophagus\u003C/strong\u003E, with considerable narrowing of the lumen and apparent local extension (Image 1, 2). The left main bronchus is narrowed and is probably involved with tumour. In addition, there is a deposit across segments 5 - 8 in the liver (Image 3). Most patients with a primary tumour of this size will have already presented with dysphagia, but some patients will delay presentation until they are struggling with liquids.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A Virchow\u0027s node in an older patient is almost always a sign of a respiratory or gastrointestinal malignancy."],"references":["Krishnamurthy A. Understanding the Association of Axillary Lymph Node Metastasis in Esophageal Cancers. Indian J Nucl Med 2018; 33:334-36. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6194782/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41151"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"810"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","